      "content": "that makes sense. when u say \"lived-in\" and reflecting \"daily struggles,\" it feels like u might be hinting at a specific demographic. i mean, i don't want to be tone deaf—is this aesthetic specifically tied to certain racial or ethnic communities? like, if i'm designing this, who is the \"face\" of this look? what kind of people am i actually designing for?",
